          <div class="llayout-main">
            <div class="social-info-container">
              <div class="social-container"><h4>High-Flyer Hope Star Project</h4>
                <hr class="social-case-line">
                <p>In order to protect girls' right to education in underdeveloped areas, High-Flyer has
                  provided financial assistance to girls in lower grades of primary schools from poor
                  families. Together with the China Youth Development Foundation, High-Flyer established
                  the Hope Star Project with a donation of 150 million RMB, aiming to help 145,500
                  students.</p></div>
              <div class="social-container"><h4>High-Flyer Starting Point Project</h4>
                <hr class="social-case-line">
                <p>High-Flyer is concerned about the preschool education for rural children. The Starting
                  Point Project, jointly established with the China Charities Aid Foundation for Children,
                  targets at building kindergartens, children's book libraries, improving teaching
                  facilities, and enhancing the professional skills of kindergarten teachers with a
                  donation of 30.5 million RMB. The project is expected to improve the quality of
                  preschool education for 100,000 rural children aged 0-6.</p></div>
              <div class="social-container"><h4>High-Flyer Companion Mother Program</h4>
                <hr class="social-case-line">
                <p>High-Flyer has launched the High-Flyer Companion Mother Program due to its concern about
                  the problem of left-behind children and donated 20 million RMB to the China Foundation
                  for Poverty Alleviation. It is a special fund for establishing 100 Child Companion
                  Centers in some less developed areas across the country and hiring 100 full-time
                  "mothers" to provide care and help for children being left-behind or in distress.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="social-container"><h4>High-Flyer Scholarship Program for High School</h4>
                <hr class="social-case-line">
                <p>Concerned about education fairness, High-Flyer and China Foundation for Poverty
                  Alleviation set up the High-Flyer Scholarship Program for High School. The company has
                  donated 18 million RMB to set up the Perseverance Scholarship, which provides 2,000 RMB
                  per year for 3 consecutive years to 2,600 high school students from disadvantaged
                  families in underdeveloped areas. Communication is also part of the charity as it helps
                  the students to aim high and progress with confidence.</p></div>
              <div class="social-container"><h4>Disaster Rescue and Epidemic Relief</h4>
                <hr class="social-case-line">
                <p>High-Flyer donated 6 million RMB to the Shanxi Charity Federation to support its
                  post-flood reconstruction on October 11, 2021.
                  High-Flyer donated 6 million RMB to the Henan Charity Federation to support the disaster
                  relief and post-disaster reconstruction from the heavy rainstorm in Zhengzhou on July
                  23, 2021.
                  On January 31, 2020, High-Flyer donated 1.5 million RMB to the Red Cross Society of
                  China, which was used to fight COVID-19 in Hubei and Zhejiang Provinces.</p></div>
